on several Elvis Presley musical films and directed Presley in the 1966 film, Paradise, Hawaiian Style for Paramount Pictures. Because of that, plus his experience directing a western film, MGM hired him to direct rock singer Roy Orbison in 1967\'s The Fastest Guitar Alive. He was the associate producer in charge of action & animal scenes for Quest for Fire. In the 1980s, Steven Spielberg hired Moore as assistant director for both the second and third Indiana Jones films. Moore worked as second unit director on Raiders of the Lost Ark. His association with Spielberg also led him to direct one episode (\"Alamo Jobe\") in the acclaimed TV series Amazing Stories. Well into his eighties, Moore was still active, his most recent work being as the second unit director for Disney\'s 2000 film, 102 Dalmatians.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Michael D. Moore, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia','1914-10-14','2013-03-04'),(3289,'Fred C. Brannon',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(3290,'Kim Sung-soo','Seoul, South Korea','Kim Sung-soo (김성수) is a South Korean film director.','1961-06-19',NULL),(3291,'Kenji Kodama','Hokkaido, Japan','Kenji Kodama (こだま 兼嗣, Kodama Kenji, born December 13, 1949), real name: 児玉 兼嗣 (same reading), is a Japanese anime director and storyboard artist born in Hokkaidō. He is a member of the Japanese Animation Creators Association (JAniCA). His wife is Sachiko Kamimura, an animator and illustrator.\n\nHe is best known for being one of the main directors on the long-running anime Case Closed, also known as Detective Conan, as well as the City Hunter series and Lupin III Part III.','1949-12-13',NULL),(3292,'Bruce A. Evans','Long Beach, California, USA','Bruce Anslie Evans (born September 19, 1946) is an American film director, producer and screenwriter best known for his work on Stand by Me (1986), Jungle 2 Jungle (1997) and Mr. Brooks (2007).\n\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia','1946-09-19',NULL),(3293,'Shinsuke Sato','H